Package: AccumulatR
Type: Package
Title: Native Likelihood Kernels for Race Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Niek", "Stevenson", email = "niek.stevenson@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: AccumulatR is a R/C++ toolkit for building simulators and likelihood for generalized race models. The package keeps the R surface intentionally tiny: you prepare a model once in R, obtain the serialized native context plus per-trial metadata, and then execute all likelihood evaluations on the C++ side.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.0)
Imports: Rcpp, RcppParallel
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppParallel, BH
SystemRequirements: C++17
NeedsCompilation: yes
LazyData: false
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Author: Niek Stevenson [aut, cre]
